The Speaker Lagos State House of Assembly, Rt. Hon. Mudashiru Obasa has said Nigeria and its citizens more than ever before require unity, love and special courage to come out of the challenge posed by COVID-19 pandemic stronger.  Obasa said this in his goodwill message to Christians in the country to mark this year’s Easter celebration amid the challenge of a spreading virus that has kept some states, including Lagos, on lockdown.  The Speaker who doubles as the chairman of the Conference of Speakers of State Legislatures, noted that where unity exists, the people show obedience to law, order and every other directive aimed at resolving challenges.  He commended executive arm of Lagos state government headed by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu for the leadership roles and perfect steps taken since COVID-19 hit Lagos.  According to him, the state government urgently requires massive encouragement from the residents at this trying time when courage is needed to tackle the spreading virus.  “This was why members of the Lagos State House of Assembly, in the wake of COVID-19, met and passed a bill granting more powers to the governor in the face of the efforts to tackle the virus,” Obasa said.  He stated further that, “At this critical time in our history, we must not only cry to God or get closer to Him, we must follow up by ensuring strict adherence to directives such as washing of hands with soap and water, using hand sanitizers where possible, maintaining social distance and giving special attention to our health”.  While enjoining constituents of the state to remain safe and cautious, he said government’s best can only reflect positively where the residents are determined to show support and love for their neighbours at this time of lockdown. 